{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "pesapal-to-life-api-collection",
		"name": "Pesapal API 3.0 - To Life Collection",
		"description": "Complete Postman collection for testing Pesapal Payment Gateway API 3.0 integration.\n\nThis collection includes all available endpoints:\n- Authentication\n- IPN Registration & Management\n- Order Submission (Standard & Recurring)\n- Transaction Status\n- Refund Requests\n- Order Cancellation\n\n## Setup Instructions\n\n1. Import this collection into Postman\n2. Edit collection variables (click collection > Variables tab)\n3. Set your consumer_key and consumer_secret\n4. Set base_url to match your environment\n5. Run 'Get Auth Token' first - token auto-saves\n6. Test other endpoints\n\n## Collection Variables (Edit these!)\n\n- `base_url`: Sandbox: https://cybqa.pesapal.com/pesapalv3 | Live: https://pay.pesapal.com/v3\n- `consumer_key`: Your Pesapal consumer key\n- `consumer_secret`: Your Pesapal consumer secret\n- `auth_token`: Auto-populated after authentication\n- `ipn_id`: Auto-populated after IPN registration\n\n## IMPORTANT\n\nMake sure base_url matches your credentials:\n- Sandbox credentials -> use sandbox URL\n- Live credentials -> use live URL\n\nDefault values use Pesapal's public demo sandbox credentials.",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "Authentication",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Get Auth Token",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
									"",
									"pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('Response has token', function () {",
									"    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('token');",
									"});",
									"",
									"// Save token to collection variables (works without environment)",
									"if (jsonData.token) {",
									"    pm.collectionVariables.set('auth_token', jsonData.token);",
									"    console.log('Token saved to collection variables');",
									"}",
									"",
									"pm.test('Token expiry date exists', function () {",
									"    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('expiryDate');",
									"});"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							},
							{
								"key": "Accept",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"consumer_key\": \"{{consumer_key}}\",\n    \"consumer_secret\": \"{{consumer_secret}}\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/Auth/RequestToken",
							"host": [
								"{{base_url}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"api",
								"Auth",
								"RequestToken"
							]
						},
						"description": "Authenticate with Pesapal API to get a bearer token.\n\nThe token is valid for 5 minutes and must be used for all subsequent API calls.\n\n**Required:**\n- consumer_key: Your Pesapal consumer key\n- consumer_secret: Your Pesapal consumer secret\n\n**Response:**\n- token: JWT bearer token\n- expiryDate: Token expiration timestamp (UTC)\n- status: Response status code"
					},
					"response": [
						{
							"name": "Success Response",
							"originalRequest": {
								"method": "POST",
								"header": [],
								"body": {
									"mode": "raw",
									"raw": "{\n    \"consumer_key\": \"your_consumer_key\",\n    \"consumer_secret\": \"your_consumer_secret\"\n}"
								},
								"url": {
									"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/Auth/RequestToken",
									"host": [
										"{{base_url}}"
									],
									"path": [
										"api",
										"Auth",
										"RequestToken"
									]
								}
							},
							"status": "OK",
							"code": 200,
							"_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
							"header": [],
							"body": "{\n    \"token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...\",\n    \"expiryDate\": \"2026-01-24T12:00:00.000Z\",\n    \"error\": null,\n    \"status\": \"200\",\n    \"message\": \"Request processed successfully\"\n}"
						}
					]
				}
			],
			"description": "Authentication endpoints for obtaining API access tokens."
		},
		{
